8.10	We recommended that the Municipal Mayor instruct:
The Municipal Treasurer to stop issuing accountable forms to erring accountable officers in order to avoid the practice of keeping collections in their hands for a long period of time;
Install control over the issuance of cash ticket and its remittance,  by designating an employee independent from Municipal Treasurer’s Office and Market Department that will randomly check the issuance of cash tickets made by the Assistant Municipal Treasurer and its remittance to the Liquidating Officer;
The Assistant Municipal Treasurer to refrain from issuing cash tickets to non-bonded employees pursuant to Section 101 of PD 1445, Section 305(f) of RA 7160, Section 50, Chapter 9, Subtitle B, Book V, EO No 292 and Bureau of Treasury, Treasury Circular No. 02-2009 dated August 5, 2009.
The Liquidating Officer (Cashier II) to stop keeping large amount of collections in her hand to avoid possible loss and misappropriation. Likewise, practice depositing the collections intact everyday regardless of the amount since the Municipal Treasurer’s Office is only less than 1 km away from their AGDB.

16.10	We recommended that the Municipal Mayor instruct:
The HRMO to explain why the scope and nature of work of the job-order workers were not included in the plantilla of contractual appointment;
The Municipal Accountant explain why no retention was made on the payment of materials in consonance with the provision of Section 62.1 of IRR of RA 9184;
The MPDC, HRMO,  BAC Chairman and the Municipal Engineer to explain the above noted observations about the procurement and implementation of the projects;
The Municipal Accountant, Municipal Engineer and BAC Chairman to submit all the lacking documents pertaining to the procurement of materials, fuel and labor to avoid suspension in audit.

17.18	We recommended that the Municipal Mayor instruct:
The HRMO to explain why the scope and nature of work of the job-order workers were not included in the plantilla of contractual appointment;
The Municipal Accountant explain why no retention was made on the payment of materials in consonance with the provision of Section 62.1 of IRR of RA 9184;
The MPDC, HRMO,  BAC Chairman and the Municipal Engineer to explain the above noted observations about the procurement and implementation of the projects;
The Municipal Accountant, Municipal Engineer and BAC Chairman to submit all the lacking documents pertaining to the procurement of materials, fuel and labor to avoid suspension in audit.

18.13	We recommended that the Municipal Mayor instruct:
The BAC Chairman to explain the noted observations in the procurement of the service vehicle;
The Municipal Treasurer to explain why payment was made before actual delivery and acceptance of the service vehicle;
The Municipal Accountant to  explain why no warranty security in the form of retention money was deducted in the payment to the supplier pursuant to the provision of Section 62.1 of the IRR of RA 9184; and
The Municipal Accountant and BAC Chairman to submit all the lacking documents to avoid suspension in audit.

19.14	We recommended that the Municipal Mayor instruct:
The HRMO to explain why the scope and nature of work of the job-order workers were not included in the plantilla of contractual appointment;
The Municipal Accountant to explain why the LGU counterpart for the project was not transferred to Trust Fund account;
The MPDC, BAC Chairman and the Municipal Engineer to explain the above noted observations about the procurement and implementation of the projects; and
The Municipal Accountant, Municipal Engineer and BAC Chairman to submit all the lacking documents pertaining to the procurement of materials and labor for both projects  to avoid suspension in audit.

19.45   We recommended that the Municipal Mayor instruct:
The Municipal Accountant to compute the liquidated damages due from the supplier for late delivery. Likewise, explain why no retention was made on the payment of materials in consonance with the provision of Section 62.1 of IRR of RA 9184;
The Municipal Agriculturist, BAC Chairman and the Municipal Accountant to explain the above noted observations about the procurement and implementation of the projects.
The Municipal Accountant and BAC Chairman to submit all the lacking documents pertaining to the procurement of high value crops.

32.9	We recommended that:
The municipal officials specially the budget office prepare the budget on due date and prioritize its deliberation and approval;
The Municipal Government Officials and member of the Local Development Council properly plan, prioritize all activities and appraise the socio-economic development programs and projects to be implemented during the year, and evaluate viability of the projects as well as the need for any additional fund needed to complete a project programmed in the previous years. Moreover, Management adopt a mode of implementation that will fast track the completion of their programmed developmental projects;
The Municipal Engineer periodically provide the status of projects undertaken by the Municipality as basis of the Municipal Budget Officer and Municipal Accountant in their periodic review and monitoring of balances of continuing appropriations, submit a list of all completed projects to support the reversion of such unexpended balance to the unappropriated surplus; and
The Municipal Budget Officer and the Municipal Accountant review and analyze the unexpended balances of appropriations of completed projects for reversion to the unappropriated surplus in accordance with Section 322 of RA 7160.
